Dury (Polish pronunciation: ; German: Döhringshof) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Morąg, within Ostróda County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south-east of Morąg,  north of Ostróda, and  west of the regional capital Olsztyn. At the 2006 census, it had a population of 40.
